1
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:10,166
♪

2
00:00:19,416 --> 00:00:20,958
I can do this myself.

3
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:23,583
[gasps]

4
00:00:24,916 --> 00:00:25,708
[gunshot]

5
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:26,625
[inhales sharply]

6
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,041
Wait. You...

7
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,125
Yumiko.

8
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:38,125
I... I didn't think
you'd actually kill him.

9
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:40,625
[YUMIKO]
You can still go back.

10
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:42,750
If you give them
an honest report,

11
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,583
well, they won't
kill you at least.

12
00:00:47,416 --> 00:00:48,583
[TAKUYA groaning]

13
00:00:54,583 --> 00:00:56,166
[KOUTA]
All this for him.

14
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:40,291
I bet it must feel
pretty pathetic

15
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:42,500
getting saved
by someone like me.

16
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:46,041
Hey, Kouta,
did you get the girl?

17
00:02:46,125 --> 00:02:48,375
You saw her, right?

18
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:50,083
[groans]
Riding with me?

19
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,291
[YUMIKO] Don't worry,
she just has a few scrapes.

20
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,541
Yumiko, this guy
isn't worth our time.

21
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:06,750
[TAKUYA]
So leave me.

22
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,750
But please save the girl.

23
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:13,250
Or else this whole mess
will have been meaningless.

24
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:16,416
Unless I save you, then this
will be meaningless for me.

25
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,791
[TAKUYA groaning]

26
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:21,291
[YUMIKO] I'll give the girl
back to the Agency.

27
00:03:21,375 --> 00:03:23,666
You'll walk away and leave
this whole mess behind you.

28
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:26,125
Isn't that enough?

29
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:29,541
Nah. It looks to me like
we're saving both of 'em.

30
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,291
We can work out
the details later.

31
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:32,291
What? No!

32
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:33,791
Come on, look at her.

33
00:03:33,875 --> 00:03:35,375
We've got no choice.

34
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:37,916
♪

35
00:03:51,916 --> 00:03:53,625
[OFFICER over radio]
This is the Metropolitan Police

36
00:03:53,708 --> 00:03:54,958
requesting backup.

37
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,375
We need a removal team
dispatched at once.

38
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:00,666
Takuya.

39
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:03,291
Please be okay.

40
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:06,958
♪

41
00:04:18,541 --> 00:04:20,250
[TAKUYA] Can't believe
our detective office

42
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:23,208
had an outpost
inside the lockdown district.

43
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:25,000
[YUMIKO]
It was set up after you quit.

44
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:30,541
This is the perfect place
to hide troublesome things.

45
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,791
[KOUTA] I'm sure
this girl's gone through a lot.

46
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:43,875
Can't believe she was imprisoned
there for three years.

47
00:04:43,958 --> 00:04:47,666
Oh, yeah. I guess I owe you
some gratitude. Thank you.

48
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:50,625
Well, I didn't
actually do it for you.

49
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,333
Damn, dude.

50
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:55,291
You've got a knack for sticking
your head into hornet's nests.

51
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:57,208
[TAKUYA]
I signed a contract.

52
00:04:57,291 --> 00:04:58,500
[YUMIKO]
I know I can't make you stop

53
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:00,166
no matter what I say, Takuya,

54
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,833
but try to be less reckless.

55
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:05,916
Right now, we need a way to get
out of the lockdown district.

56
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:19,708
I get it.

57
00:05:19,791 --> 00:05:22,125
But first,
I wanna get my bike fixed.

58
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:24,208
Can you help me
get a hold of Geek?

59
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:26,416
I lost my phone somewhere.

60
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:27,708
Who's Geek?

61
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:29,333
[TAKUYA] I think
you worked with him once.

62
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:30,958
He's a childhood friend of mine.

63
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:32,333
[groans sharply]

64
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:34,958
[YUMIKO] Hold on.
Let me check the database.

65
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:37,416
Are you talkin' about
that chubby shut-in?

66
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,208
There's a little more
to him than that.

67
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:41,958
I'm sure he knows
where my bike is.

68
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:44,083
[YUMIKO]
No luck.

69
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:47,458
We'll have to
lure him out somehow.

70
00:05:47,541 --> 00:05:49,500
♪

71
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:55,875
-[laptop chimes]
-[ALL inhale sharply]

72
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:57,833
[YUMIKO]
There. Got him.

73
00:05:57,916 --> 00:05:59,375
[KOUTA]
That was quick.

74
00:05:59,458 --> 00:06:01,666
[YUMIKO]
If this guy's useful,

75
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:04,083
we can start
including him in our plans.

76
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,583
[TAKUYA]
Be careful where you go.

77
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:22,375
We can't have you
getting spotted.

78
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:29,541
Eat this. You're gonna need it.

79
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,375
-[YUKI] I'm sorry.
-Hmm?

80
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,416
[YUKI]
That you're hurt.

81
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,125
[TAKUYA]
Oh. Yeah.

82
00:06:36,208 --> 00:06:38,875
I got myself caught up
in a real mess.

83
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:42,250
But it's not on you.
I signed the contract.

84
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,750
[stomach growling]

85
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,208
[wrapper crunches]

86
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:50,458
[TAKUYA]
Wanna split it?

87
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:52,458
♪

88
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:05,833
[wind whistling]

89
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:12,125
[TAKUYA] The gunman who saved us
on the expressway,

90
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:16,333
did you summon him
there somehow?

91
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:17,666
[YUKI]
No idea.

92
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:19,625
But I know who he is.

93
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:21,833
Akira.

94
00:07:23,083 --> 00:07:25,208
He was my father's escort.

95
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:28,750
Escort? Oh, like a bodyguard.

96
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:31,583
Don't suppose you know enough to
guess why he's a Tama-shi now.

97
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,041
[YUKI]
He was caught up in the Lost.

98
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,875
Right in front of me.

99
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:39,125
It wasn't just him.

100
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:42,291
My father, my little brother.

101
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:46,166
They're gone.
They all disappeared.

102
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:51,583
[TAKUYA]
I see. Wonder what it is.

103
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:53,000
The Lost, I mean.

104
00:07:53,083 --> 00:07:56,458
We can't even tell
if it was caused by nature.

105
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:59,625
For all we know,
it could happen again tomorrow.

106
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:02,000
Don't guess you'd wanna
talk about what you saw.

107
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:14,666
[wind howling]

108
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,166
[YUKI gasps]

109
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:19,208
[TAKUYA]
Must be past your bedtime.

110
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:20,791
[YUKI]
Don't make fun of me.

111
00:08:27,916 --> 00:08:29,916
[EIJI]
Two gravitational anomalies.

112
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,291
Picked up one in the afternoon,
and another in the evening.

113
00:08:33,375 --> 00:08:36,833
And the first of those anomalies
began just as the monk appeared.

114
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:39,875
We've got it.

115
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:43,166
Empirical proof
of a Tama-shi's appearance.

116
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,541
[YUMIKO]
It's no good.

117
00:08:50,541 --> 00:08:53,583
All the back streets
are being monitored too.

118
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,208
So there's no choice.

119
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:57,875
Right.

120
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:02,958
Let's go.

121
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:04,083
[KOUTA]
Say what?

122
00:09:04,166 --> 00:09:05,875
Who said you get
to take the lead?

123
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:09,500
Same old Takuya.

124
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:12,666
Come on. Let's follow.

125
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:16,416
[YUKI]
'Kay.

126
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:20,625
♪

127
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:36,916
[ALL panting]

128
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:43,916
-[YUMIKO] You okay?
-[YUKI] Mm-hmm.

129
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,791
The next station isn't too far.

130
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:48,875
And it comes up outside
the lockdown district.

131
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:51,791
Damn it.
The Agency is persistent.

132
00:09:51,875 --> 00:09:54,708
What exactly are they?
The police know about them?

133
00:09:54,791 --> 00:09:56,750
What about the government?

134
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:58,541
[YUMIKO] Even as members,
Kouta and I weren't able

135
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,291
to get a full picture of it.

136
00:10:00,375 --> 00:10:03,250
The Agency isn't really
a traditional organization.

137
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,875
I'd describe it
as more of an alliance

138
00:10:04,958 --> 00:10:06,750
of like-minded individuals.

139
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:09,541
The main thing that stood out
to me was how creepy it was.

140
00:10:10,708 --> 00:10:13,541
I wish our office would pick who
they work with more carefully.

141
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:16,625
[gasps]

142
00:10:18,791 --> 00:10:19,791
[KOUTA gasps]

143
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,333
[footsteps]

144
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:27,833
[YUKI gasps]

145
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,041
Suzuna.

146
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:30,583
Damn it.

147
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:33,416
[SUZUNA] Did you really think
we wouldn't expect this?

148
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,166
Kouta.

149
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:43,250
♪

150
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:47,125
[YUKI gasps]

151
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:51,000
Hurry!

152
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:52,333
-[door closes]
-[KOUTA gasps]

153
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:54,791
[gunshot]

154
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:56,166
[YUMIKO grunts]

155
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:59,166
Yumiko, no!

156
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:00,125
Did she just...

157
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:02,166
[KOUTA grunting]

158
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:07,250
[door thudding]

159
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,083
It's done. Let's go.

160
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:17,250
There's no point trying
to get through that door now.

161
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:19,875
And since you're here,
I have something to say.

162
00:11:21,708 --> 00:11:23,375
Cut off their escape.

163
00:11:30,041 --> 00:11:31,208
Now, then...

164
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:38,208
It looks like you don't have
any interest in talking.

165
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,458
[gunshot]

166
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,083
[ALL panting]

167
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:50,250
[footsteps approaching]

168
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:51,458
[TAKUYA]
Shit.

169
00:11:51,541 --> 00:11:53,583
[gasps]

170
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:54,916
[grunts]

171
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,333
Let's make a stand here.

172
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:57,500
[footsteps receding]

173
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,875
Huh? Hey. Wait!

174
00:12:05,583 --> 00:12:06,708
Come on, Takuya.

175
00:12:06,791 --> 00:12:08,458
At least tell me
what you're planning.

176
00:12:08,541 --> 00:12:10,708
Why are you ignoring me?!

177
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:13,083
♪

178
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:16,250
[panting]

179
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,208
[groans sharply]

180
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,666
[YUMIKO]
You made me a promise.

181
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,500
You promised me
Takuya would be safe!

182
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:28,416
The higher-ups
made their choice.

183
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,375
It must be nice for you.

184
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:33,166
Going through life without ever
having to think for yourself.

185
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:35,791
Is this what thinking
for yourself looks like?

186
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:38,333
Then I'm glad I'm not dumb
enough to do the same.

187
00:12:39,416 --> 00:12:40,958
[BOTH grunting]

188
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:43,833
-[gunshot]
-[YUMIKO gasps]

189
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:46,583
Why'd you betray
the Agency, Yumiko?

190
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:48,291
Don't you value
your own life at all?

191
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:51,375
If I die today,
at least I'll die free.

192
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,541
It's better than living
as someone's dog.

193
00:12:53,625 --> 00:12:55,708
You're doing all this
for that man.

194
00:12:55,791 --> 00:12:57,291
Why would you go this far?

195
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,041
[YUMIKO]
Because I love him.

196
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:02,500
[door slams]

197
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:03,833
[TAKUYA]
Yuki, take cover.

198
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,291
Shit!

199
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:08,625
You handle the right side,

200
00:13:08,708 --> 00:13:10,208
-I'll take the left.
-[gunfire]

201
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:11,750
[MEN groan]

202
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:14,000
Thought you were gonna
deal with the left.

203
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:15,000
What's wrong?

204
00:13:17,041 --> 00:13:18,208
[gunfire]

205
00:13:18,291 --> 00:13:19,791
[MEN coughing]

206
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,750
Pretty good. I mean,
I could have done it too.

207
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:26,333
All right,
if we can get to the surface,

208
00:13:26,416 --> 00:13:28,250
we'll be out
of the lockdown district.

209
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:29,750
[gasps]

210
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:33,583
[YUKI] What about your friend?
We're leaving her?

211
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,291
She'll be all right.

212
00:13:38,375 --> 00:13:40,125
Yumiko always
figures out a way

213
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,750
for everyone
to make it through.

214
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:44,291
[YUKI softly]
Hmm.

215
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:45,666
The exit's locked,

216
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,250
so we can't
just take the stairs.

217
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:49,750
Need to take
a little detour first.

218
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:53,291
You know,
I think you've changed a bit.

219
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:54,666
Huh?

220
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,708
The Kouta that I used to know

221
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:58,958
wouldn't have taken
this thankless job.

222
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,000
Is that what you think?

223
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:03,833
Whatever.

224
00:14:03,916 --> 00:14:06,583
I feel like jobs like this
make life more interesting.

225
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:09,666
I mean, I only get to live once.

226
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:12,416
So I may as well
keep things exciting, you know?

227
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:15,708
While we're on the subject,
you've changed some yourself.

228
00:14:17,541 --> 00:14:18,791
[TAKUYA]
How do you mean?

229
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,541
[KOUTA sighs]
No point in explaining it.

230
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:31,083
Whew. Got it.

231
00:14:33,125 --> 00:14:35,041
I'm sure you're full
of questions, Yuki.

232
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:37,041
I'll tell you
my heroic stories later.

233
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,125
[YUKI]
That's okay.

234
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:39,333
[KOUTA]
What do you mean?

235
00:14:39,416 --> 00:14:41,208
They're super interesting,
I promise.

236
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:43,000
Back in the day,
our office used to get

237
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,041
some very important missions
from the government.

238
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:46,250
Hey.

239
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:47,916
You're such a stiff, Takuya.

240
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,916
What's the harm
in tellin' her now?

241
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,500
So, yeah, on this one miss--

242
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:52,750
-[flesh squelches]
-[KOUTA groans]

243
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:56,500
[TAKUYA]
Kouta? What's wrong?

244
00:14:56,583 --> 00:14:58,041
[KOUTA weakly]
I...

245
00:14:59,416 --> 00:15:00,625
[groans]

246
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:02,041
-[TAKUYA] Kouta!
-[YUKI gasps]

247
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:06,250
[coughing]

248
00:15:08,291 --> 00:15:10,458
[YUKI whimpers]

249
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:11,958
[TAKUYA grunts, gasps]

250
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:14,208
[groaning]

251
00:15:15,541 --> 00:15:16,500
[grunts]

252
00:15:20,541 --> 00:15:21,750
Just go!

253
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,208
Get her... out.

254
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:26,916
[grunts]

255
00:15:28,958 --> 00:15:30,333
Kouta, no!

256
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:32,375
-[TAKUYA] Come on.
-[YUKI] Get up! Come with us!

257
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:34,916
♪

258
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:42,375
Well, damn.

259
00:15:42,458 --> 00:15:44,166
So much for exciting.

260
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,208
[groans]

261
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:57,958
[KOUTA
groaning weakly]

262
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,916
Shit, man.

263
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:07,750
That really friggin' hurts!

264
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:09,000
[gunshot]

265
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:11,583
[TAKUYA and YUKI panting]

266
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,666
[YUKI]
Hold on!

267
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,416
[YUKI grunting]

268
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:21,291
[TAKUYA]
What?

269
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:23,500
Your friends.

270
00:16:23,583 --> 00:16:25,250
[TAKUYA exhales sharply]

271
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:26,666
How are you moving forward

272
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,375
when you know
they might be dead?

273
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:36,875
[BOTH gasp]

274
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,041
[BOTH grunt]

275
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,541
[gasps]

276
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,000
[TAKUYA]
It's him.

277
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:48,958
[YUKI gasps]

278
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:50,791
[YUKI]
A Tama-shi?

279
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:57,750
[BOTH gasp]

280
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:02,458
[YUKI gasping]

281
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:04,708
[YUKI screams]

282
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:06,416
[MAN shuddering]

283
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:08,666
[engine revving]

284
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,041
Get in the truck, hurry!

285
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:13,583
♪

286
00:17:15,875 --> 00:17:17,916
[TAKUYA panting]

287
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,375
Timely as always.

288
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:23,083
Wait. Why are you driving us
this way?

289
00:17:23,166 --> 00:17:24,875
No choice.

290
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:27,708
I know you were trying to get
out of the lockdown district,

291
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,875
but we're getting chased
by something freaky.

292
00:17:29,958 --> 00:17:31,541
It sounds like a swarm
of pissed off hornets.

293
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:32,791
[BOTH gasp]

294
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,541
[GEEK] What the hell
are we up against?

295
00:17:34,625 --> 00:17:36,666
♪

296
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,083
[TAKUYA]
That knife is the key.

297
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:45,041
Geek, did you fix the bike?

298
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:46,791
Yeah, I got it
running at least.

299
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:49,458
But what are you
planning to do?

300
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:52,458
Whatever I can
to distract the thing.

301
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,458
You two take this chance
to escape.

302
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:55,791
-[YUKI gasps]
-Huh?!

303
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:57,083
What are you
talking about, Takuya?!

304
00:17:57,166 --> 00:17:59,083
Don't be crazy!

305
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,833
Come back, please!

306
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:02,583
[engine starts]

307
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,666
[YUKI] Why would you go
this far for me?

308
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:08,083
[TAKUYA] Because that's
what I wanna do.

309
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:09,375
[YUKI gasps]

310
00:18:15,375 --> 00:18:17,291
Huh? No! Hold on!

311
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:20,083
[TAKUYA] Always hated hornets.
Let's do this!

312
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:22,333
[grunts]

313
00:18:32,416 --> 00:18:34,458
You think this is
some kinda joke?

314
00:18:34,541 --> 00:18:37,208
The hell possessed you
to jump after me?

315
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:41,583
I'm sorry,
but I did it cause I wanted to.

316
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,708
Please try to buy me
some time.

317
00:18:46,791 --> 00:18:50,708
[TAKUYA] Huh. I'm starting
to get how this guy works.

318
00:18:50,791 --> 00:18:52,291
Hang on tight, Yuki.

319
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:01,708
[tires screech]

320
00:19:07,541 --> 00:19:08,875
[TAKUYA]
Just as I thought.

321
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:12,916
[grunts]

322
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:23,791
Seems like this knife is
the only thing you attack with.

323
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:27,250
You must be pretty
attached to it, huh?

324
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:30,291
Give... it... back.

325
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:31,666
-[beeps]
-[TAKUYA gasps]

326
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:32,833
[grunting]

327
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:37,625
[MAN]
Give... it... back.

328
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:38,958
[TAKUYA grunting]

329
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:46,250
[TAKUYA gasps]

330
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:47,541
[gunshots]

331
00:19:55,958 --> 00:19:57,041
[groans]

332
00:19:57,125 --> 00:19:58,958
[yells]

333
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:00,166
[BOTH scream]

334
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:05,708
[AKIRA groaning]

335
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:08,625
[YUKI]
Akira!

336
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:14,333
[gunfire]

337
00:20:14,416 --> 00:20:15,375
[gasps sharply]

338
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:16,958
[explosion]

339
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:19,750
[BOTH panting]

340
00:20:22,166 --> 00:20:24,458
♪

341
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:28,000
[panting]

342
00:20:32,708 --> 00:20:35,250
[AKIRA] Looks like I can
protect you again, Miss Yuki.

343
00:20:37,166 --> 00:20:40,166
[YUKI]
Thanks. It's good to see you.

344
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,583
That time was different.

345
00:20:45,666 --> 00:20:47,500
You knew he would come, right?

346
00:20:47,583 --> 00:20:49,875
♪

347
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:53,833
[YUKI]
Hmm.

348
00:20:55,541 --> 00:20:57,833
[GEEK]
Hey!

349
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:59,333
[panting]

350
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:09,375
It seems she's awakened at last.

351
00:21:09,458 --> 00:21:10,708
[YUMIKO shudders]

352
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,250
[SUZUNA] Then I shouldn't
overwrite things any further.

353
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:23,291
[TAKUYA]
You saved me. Thanks.

354
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:26,000
[YUKI]
Well, you did save me first.

355
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:27,916
To be honest,
against the Tama-shi,

356
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,083
I'm helpless.

357
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:30,166
This is a bum deal.

358
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:32,333
But I can't handle this job.

359
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:34,166
Not without that power of yours.

360
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,708
Will you help me?

361
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:40,416
I'm going back.

362
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,708
[TAKUYA]
Hmm?

363
00:21:41,791 --> 00:21:44,375
[YUKI] I want to confirm
my father's fate.

364
00:21:44,458 --> 00:21:46,291
See it with my own eyes.

365
00:21:48,541 --> 00:21:49,875
Understood.

366
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:52,666
Before we do that,
let's get Yumiko and Kouta.

367
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:55,000
♪

368
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:40,083
♪

369
00:23:40,166 --> 00:23:42,500
[inaudible]

370
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,250
[YUKI]
Next Episode, "Memory."

